    <div class="py-5 px-5 last:rounded-b-lg dark:bg-gray-900 first:rounded-t-lg" hidden="">
        <p class="mb-2 text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">The main difference is that the core components from Flowbite are open source under the MIT license, whereas Tailwind UI is a paid product. Another difference is that Flowbite relies on smaller and standalone components, whereas Tailwind UI offers
            sections of pages.</p>
        <p class="mb-2 text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">However, we actually recommend using both Flowbite, Flowbite Pro, and even Tailwind UI as there is no technical reason stopping you from using the best of two worlds.</p>
